Here is the comprehensive, FAANG-inspired handover document and master prompt you can provide directly to your coding assistant to build this system.

1. Final Aim & Expected Output

The Final Aim: To build a secure, chatbot-like interface and agentic AI model that answers user queries based on EDA (Electronic Design Automation) output results stored on a RHEL VM. The system acts as a dynamic "librarian" that can navigate directories and extract specific data points.


The Expected Output: A fully functional, decoupled architecture featuring a vanilla JavaScript chat interface that communicates via a REST API to a Python Flask backend. The backend will use LangChain and a corporate JedAI LLM endpoint to intelligently route user queries to pure Python, read-only data extraction tools.

2. System End-to-End Principles & Design Constraints
Before writing any code, the AI assistant must understand these immutable rules:


Zero Shell Execution: The agent is strictly prohibited from executing OS-level commands (e.g., free -g, grep, awk).


Pure Python Read-Only: All data retrieval must be done using pure Python file I/O operations operating strictly in read-only mode.


Corporate Data Privacy: No public or commercial AI endpoints (like standard OpenAI) may be used. The AI orchestration must route exclusively through the internal, OpenAI-compatible JedAI API.

Stateless JSON Transport: The system must not dump massive files into the LLM context window. The API will perform the targeted extraction and return concise JSON payloads for the LLM to synthesize. The data must be "forgotten" immediately after the response is generated.


Native Execution Environment: The code will run natively on a RHEL VM accessed via a VS Code Remote-SSH connection from a Windows machine.

3. The Master Copilot Prompt
Copy and paste the text block below directly into GitHub Copilot or your designated AI assistant to generate the entire codebase step-by-step.

System Role: You are an expert Principal Software Engineer. Your task is to build a secure, read-only Agentic RAG system for an EDA (Electronic Design Automation) environment. The environment runs on a RHEL VM, accessed via VS Code Remote-SSH.

Core Constraints:

You must use Flask for the backend API and Vanilla HTML/JS/CSS for the frontend.

You must use LangChain with the ChatOpenAI wrapper to connect to a custom corporate endpoint (JedAI).

ABSOLUTELY NO OS shell command execution (no subprocess, os.system, etc.). All tools provided to the LangChain agent must be pure Python read-only file parsers.

You must implement a directory traversal security check to prevent the API from reading files outside a defined base workspace.

